quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  97,1,"Behold, We revealed this (Qur'an) on the Night of Power.{1}",footnotes:1:The words in the original are anzalana hu: We sent it  down. But although there is no mention of the Quran before it
  97,2,"And what do you know what the Night of Power is?"
  97,3,"The Night of Power is better than a thousand months.{1}",footnotes:1:The commentators in general have understood this to mean that the good acts performed in this night are superior in value to the good acts of a thousand months in which Lailat-ul-qadr is not included. There is no doubt that this is in itself correct and the Prophet (peace be upon him) has described great excellences and virtues of the good acts and devotions of this night. According to a tradition related in Bukhari and Muslim
  97,4,"The angels along with the Spirit{1} descend in it by the permission of their Lord{2} with all kinds of decrees.",footnotes:1:[The Spirit: Gabriel, who has been mentioned separately from the angels in view of his unique eminence, honor and merit.],footnotes:2:[That is, they do not descend of their own accord but by leave of their Lord, and every decree implies amr hakim (a wise decree) as described in (Surah Ad-Dukhan, Ayat 5).]
  97,5,"All peace is that night until the rise of dawn.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, the entire night, from evening till morning, is peace, free from every evil and mischief.
  98,1,"Those who disbelieved{1} – be they from the People of the Book or from those who associated{2} others with Allah in His Divinity – will not desist from unbelief until the Clear Proof should come to them;{3}",footnotes:1:[Here the word kufr],footnotes:2:[(unbelief) has been used],footnotes:3:[in its widest]
  98,2,"a Messenger{1} from Allah, reciting from Purified Scrolls;{2}",footnotes:1:[Here, the Prophet (peace be],footnotes:2:[upon him) has been called]
  98,3,"in writings wherein are scriptures, absolutely true and unerring."
  98,4,"Nor did those to whom the Book had been given split up until after the Proof (of the Right Way) had come to them.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, the reason why the people of the Book before
  98,5,"Yet all that they had been commanded was that they serve Allah, with utter sincerity, devoting themselves exclusively to Him, and that they establish Prayer and pay Zakah. That is the Right Faith.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, the message of the same religion, which now the
  98,6,"Those who disbelieved{1} – be they from among the People of the Book or among those who associated others with Allah in His Divinity– shall be in the Fire, and will abide in it. They are the worst of creatures.{2}",footnotes:1:[Disbelieved:Refused to acknowledge the Prophet],footnotes:2:[Refused to acknowledge the Prophet]
  98,7,"But those that believe and work righteous deeds, they are the best of creatures.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, they are superior to all creatures of God, even
